  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan: Supporting the National Justice Sector Strategy (NJSS): Fostering Increased Effectiveness in the Rule of Law</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To enhance the capacity of legal professionals within the Afghan Ministry of Justice and Supreme Courts in the 34 provinces of Afghanistan, as well as members of the Afghanistan Independent Bar Association (AIBA). 2) To increase awareness of the role of these institutions, as well as the quality of their legal services.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Professionals from the Ministry of Justice, the Supreme Court and Members from the Afghanistan Independent Bar Association (AIBA).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to improve the quality and delivery of sustainable decentralized justice services and ensuring a level of professionalism in substantive law and judicial ethics throughout Afghanistan.</narrative>
  </description>
